King Juan Carlos I of Spain visited the White House and had lunch with President Obama, Secretary Clinton, and National Security Advisor General Jones. They discussed the strong bonds between the American and Spanish people and expressed their interest in strengthening the partnership between the two countries. They also discussed common challenges such as the global economy, climate change, terrorism, and Afghanistan. The leaders also talked about the situation in the Middle East, as well as issues in Latin America and the Caribbean, including Cuba and ongoing relief efforts in Haiti.